http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Kummanam-warns-of-political-undercurrents/article14002200.ece

BJP State president Kummanam Rajasekharan has hinted at strong undercurrents and political polarisation in the ensuing Assembly elections in the State.Speaking at a meeting organised to mark the merger of the Kerala Congress (Nationalist) with the BJP, Mr. Rajasekharan said people were disgusted at the non-performance of both the LDF and the UDF and were looking forward to the BJP for the leadership.He came down on CPI(M) Polit Bureau member Pinarayi Vijayan and KPCC president V.M. Sudheeran, who according him, were trying to sell worn-out slogans to the people. The BJP when in power will implement a more imaginative development policy than the two coalitions were claiming to implement, he added.Noble Mathew, chairman, KC(N) presided over the meeting. BJP national executive member Alphons Kannanthanam, State secretary Narayanan Namboothiri, treasurer M.B. Rajagopal and others spoke.